This paper deals with 3D shape completion and inpainting using deep learning techniques, specifically convolutional neural networks and generative adversarial networks. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of recurrent neural networks, which are commonly used in natural language processing and time-series analysis, indicating a possible connection to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with 3D models, which suggests a possible connection to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
